It should be noted that when you wish to double the root of a square, either a definite root or a surd, you multiply 2 by 2 and multiply the given square by this product. A similar note on fractions

If you have it in mind to obtain half of the root, multiply one-half by one-half, then the given square by the product. The root 01 this final product gives the desired result. Similarly if you wish to have a third part, multiply a third part by a third part, and so on.
